  "text": "The Rust borrow checker's MIR analysis traces through the following key components:\n\n1. **Entry Point - mir_borrowck** (compiler/rustc_borrowck/src/lib.rs:117): The query provider that begins borrow checking for a given function definition, checking all nested bodies.\n\n2. **Root Context Dispatcher - do_mir_borrowck** (compiler/rustc_borrowck/src/root_cx.rs:242): Coordinates borrow checking for all nested bodies by collecting region constraints and handling opaque types.\n\n3. **Region Constraint Collection - borrowck_collect_region_constraints** (compiler/rustc_borrowck/src/lib.rs:309): The main analysis function that orchestrates: (a) MIR region replacement using NLL variables, (b) Borrow set construction, (c) MIR type checking with constraint generation, and (d) Move data tracking.\n\n4. **MIR Type Checking - type_check** (compiler/rustc_borrowck/src/type_check/mod.rs:98): Performs type checking of the MIR body and generates region outlives constraints and liveness requirements.\n\n5. **Live Range Calculation - type_check/liveness** (compiler/rustc_borrowck/src/type_check/liveness/mod.rs): The generate function calls trace (compiler/rustc_borrowck/src/type_check/liveness/trace.rs) which computes liveness information by backtracking through the CFG from uses to definitions, determining when each region is live at each location.\n\n6. **Borrow Set Construction - BorrowSet** (compiler/rustc_borrowck/src/borrow_set.rs:16): Gathers all borrows in the function and tracks their reservation and activation locations, particularly for two-phase borrows identified by BorrowData structures.\n\n7. **Place Conflict Detection - places_conflict** (compiler/rustc_borrowck/src/places_conflict.rs:81): Helper function that checks if two places conflict with a mutable borrow. The core analysis is in borrow_conflicts_with_place (line 104) which iterates through place projections in lockstep, using place_components_conflict to determine if projections are equal or disjoint at each step.\n\n8. **Two-Phase Borrow Resolution - check_activations** (compiler/rustc_borrowck/src/lib.rs:1823): Checks two-phase borrow activations to ensure that activating a borrow doesn't conflict with existing borrows. Two-phase activation information is stored in TwoPhaseActivation enum in borrow_set.rs.\n\n9. **NLL Region Computation - compute_regions** (compiler/rustc_borrowck/src/nll.rs:113): Computes non-lexical lifetimes by creating a RegionInferenceContext, applying Polonius facts if enabled, and solving region constraints.\n\n10. **Region Inference Context** (compiler/rustc_borrowck/src/region_infer/mod.rs:79): Manages region inference with methods to propagate constraints and check type tests. Initialized with LoweredConstraints containing outlives constraints, type tests, and liveness constraints (LivenessValues from region_infer/values.rs).\n\n11. **Constraint Solving - solve** (compiler/rustc_borrowck/src/region_infer/mod.rs:493): Propagates outlives constraints through the region SCC graph, checks type tests for unsatisfiable constraints, and computes closure region requirements if needed.\n\n12. **Liveness Values Storage - LivenessValues** (compiler/rustc_borrowck/src/region_infer/values.rs:41): Stores the liveness information for regions, mapping from regions to the set of locations where they are live, used by the region inference engine to validate region constraints.\n\nThe analysis chain integrates MIR type checking, liveness analysis, place conflict detection, two-phase borrow handling, and constraint-based region inference to determine validity of borrows and compute required lifetime relationships."
}

